SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1051
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR TRENT.
5611S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapters 160 and 173, RSMo, by adding thereto four new sections relating to protections
against discrimination in educational settings.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapters 160 and 173, RSMo, are amended by
2 adding thereto four new sections, to be known as sections
3 160.014, 160.015, 173.001, and 173.002, to read as follows:
1 160.014. 1. As used in this section and section
2 160.015, the following terms mean:
3 (1) "Antisemitism" or "antisemitic", the International
4 Holocaust Remembrance Alliance's (IHRA) Working Definition
5 of Antisemitism, including its contemporary examples, as it
6 was adopted on May 26, 2016, as a tool and guide for
7 recognizing and combating antisemitism;
8 (2) "Educational institution", each public school and
9 school district in this state.
10 2. Each educational institution shall treat harassment
11 or discrimination against students or employees or resulting
12 from institutional policies or programs on such educational
13 institution's campuses that is motivated by or including
14 antisemitism in an identical manner to discrimination
15 motivated by race.
16 3. (1) Each educational institution shall integrate
17 the definition of antisemitism in this section into such

SB 1051 2
18 educational institution's student, faculty, and employee
19 codes of conduct and shall prohibit such conduct at or by
20 such educational institution if such conduct creates an
21 atmosphere or circumstance in which individuals working at,
22 visiting, or attending the educational institution are
23 impeded from their normal course of work, study, or access
24 to the educational institution and the educational
25 institution's services and facilities either by physically
26 impeding such activity or by creating an atmosphere of fear
27 or intimidation.
28 (2) Prohibited conduct as it relates specifically to
29 antisemitism shall be incorporated into such educational
30 institution's student, faculty, and employee codes of
31 conduct and shall include penalties for harassment of and
32 discrimination against Jews in compliance with
33 antidiscrimination regulations promulgated under Title VI of
34 the federal Civil Rights Act of 1964, as amended, by the
35 United States Department of Education and the United States
36 Department of Justice.
37 4. (1) Criticism of Israel that is similar to
38 criticism toward any other country shall not be construed to
39 be antisemitic.
40 (2) Nothing in this section shall be construed to
41 diminish or infringe upon any right protected under the
42 First Amendment to the Constitution of the United States or
43 the Constitution of Missouri.
44 (3) Nothing in this section shall be construed to
45 conflict with federal or state discrimination laws.
1 160.015. 1. (1) No educational institution shall
2 discriminate because of race, ethnicity, national origin,
3 sex, disability, religion, or marital status against a
4 student or an employee of any educational institution.

SB 1051 3
5 (2) No person in this state shall, on the basis of
6 race, ethnicity, national origin, sex, disability, religion,
7 or marital status, be excluded from participation in, denied
8 the benefits of, or subjected to discrimination under any
9 program or activity or in any employment conditions or
10 practices conducted by an educational institution that
11 receives or benefits from federal or state financial
12 assistance.
13 2. An educational institution's criteria for admission
14 to a program or course shall not have the effect of
15 restricting access by persons of a particular race,
16 ethnicity, national origin, sex, disability, religion, or
17 marital status.
18 3. (1) All of an educational institution's classes
19 shall be available to all students without regard to race,
20 ethnicity, national origin, sex, disability, religion, or
21 marital status.
22 (2) This subsection shall not be construed to
23 eliminate the provision of programs designed to meet the
24 needs of students with limited proficiency in English,
25 gifted students, or students with disabilities or programs
26 tailored to students with specialized talents or skills.
27 4. Guidance services, counseling services, and
28 financial assistance services in an educational institution
29 shall be available to all students equally and provided in
30 the same manner regardless of race, ethnicity, national
31 origin, sex, disability, religion, or marital status.
32 5. All education programs, activities, and
33 opportunities offered by educational institutions shall be
34 made available without discrimination on the basis of race,
35 ethnicity, national origin, sex, disability, religion, or
36 marital status.

SB 1051 4
37 6. (1) Nothing in this section shall be construed to
38 diminish or infringe upon any right protected under the
39 First Amendment to the Constitution of the United States or
40 the Constitution of Missouri.
41 (2) Nothing in this section shall be construed to
42 conflict with federal or state discrimination laws.
43 7. (1) Each educational institution shall report
44 incidents and complaints of antisemitic discrimination or
45 harassment to the Title VI coordinator at the department of
46 elementary and secondary education.
47 (2) The Title VI coordinator shall establish,
48 maintain, and publicize a formal reporting process whereby
49 students, parents, staff, and faculty can submit complaints
50 of antisemitic discrimination and harassment.
51 (3) The Title VI coordinator shall thoroughly
52 investigate all complaints made under this subsection.
53 After a reasonable investigation, if the coordinator
54 determines that an educational institution has engaged in,
55 allowed, or failed to sufficiently prohibit antisemitic
56 discrimination or harassment, the department of elementary
57 and secondary education shall notify, in writing, the
58 educational institution of such determination and that such
59 educational institution is required to address the issues
60 described in such determination within thirty days after
61 receipt of such written notice.
62 (4) After the expiration of the thirty days to address
63 issues in the coordinator's determination, if the Title VI
64 coordinator determines the educational institution has
65 failed to take the necessary actions to address such issues,
66 the department of elementary and secondary education shall
67 report the coordinator's determination to the United States
68 Department of Education and the United States Department of

SB 1051 5
69 Justice by making a complaint under Title VI of the federal
70 Civil Rights Act of 1964, as amended.
71 (5) The Title VI coordinator shall compile an annual
72 report on complaints of antisemitic discrimination and
73 harassment monitored, reported, and investigated under this
74 section. Such report shall be published on the website of
75 the department of elementary and secondary education and
76 submitted to the general assembly before July first of each
77 year.
1 173.001. 1. As used in this section and section
2 173.002, the following terms mean:
3 (1) "Antisemitism" or "antisemitic", the International
4 Holocaust Remembrance Alliance's (IHRA) Working Definition
5 of Antisemitism, including its contemporary examples, as it
6 was adopted on May 26, 2016, as a tool and guide for
7 recognizing and combating antisemitism;
8 (2) "Educational institution", a public postsecondary
9 educational institution governed or supervised by a:
10 (a) Board erected under chapter 172, 174, 175, or 178;
11 (b) Board of trustees of a community college; or
12 (c) State board for any other technical school.
13 2. Each educational institution shall treat harassment
14 or discrimination against students or employees or resulting
15 from institutional policies or programs on such educational
16 institution's campuses that is motivated by or including
17 antisemitism in an identical manner to discrimination
18 motivated by race.
19 3. (1) Each educational institution shall integrate
20 the definition of antisemitism in this section into such
21 educational institution's student, faculty, and employee
22 codes of conduct and shall prohibit such conduct at or by
23 such educational institution if such conduct creates an

